casebody.data:
State of Connecticut v. Victor Rusgaitis (7124)

Borden, Daly and Norcott, Js.

Argued June 15 — decision released June 21, 1989 Victor Rusgaitis, pro se, the appellant (defendant). Geoffrey E. Marion, deputy assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were John A. Connelly, state’s attorney, and Karen Diebolt, deputy assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

There is no error.
